# gen213 (cardinal KB-first principle, SUBSTRING cues): the fragments that signal a
# brevity request live in the KB (intent_cue(brevity, …) in kb/core/intents.p0), matched
# anywhere in the turn by kb_cue_match — the KB-backed form of a hardcoded
# cue(norm,"…")||cue(norm,"…") chain. Here a brand-new cue is taught interactively and
# fires on the next turn, no code edit. (The teach handler runs before the matcher so the
# teaching utterance, which itself contains "short", isn't consumed as a brevity request.)
> learn "be concise" as asking for short answers
< Got it - I'll take "be concise" as asking for short answers now.
> be concise please
< Got it: I will keep it short.
